				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Why are bards so uber???<a name="29063"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 20 04 12:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Play a necro or a mage sometime. To me those classes are more 'overpowered' than bards, in some ways.
<br />

<br />
I think a ranger is pretty neat.
<br />

<br />
I have had friends who play eq come watch me at my keyboard play my bard and they say no way.  They watched me solo and decided, yeah, a bards the ticket...then they made one and said bah, I'd rather play my druid/wiz/enchanter/monk...etc. The bard is just too hard (or more likely too much work) for them.
<br />

<br />
I do feel for the classes with no diversity.  Any decent cleric can get a group most times, but they don't have the options you do as a bard.
<br />

<br />
Probably the greatest bard envy is because of our diversity. We can solo and are desireable for multiple roles in a group.
<br />

<br />
They love our damage bonus songs....but that bonus does squat for us. Then love mana regen but that regen does squat for us....they would love to solo, but aren't interested in the carpal tunnel syndrome that comes with it.
<br />

<br />
I have met a lot of alt bards in their mid thirties who are running out of steam (twinking can only take you so far) because they never learned to build and use a good twist.
<br />

<br />
I three box a tank/cleric/wizzy some. Its easier than playing the bard, in most instances.</span></td>
