			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Why are bards so uber???<a name="29082"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 20 04 2:59 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Just wondering, I know that a ton of people that I know think that bards should be nerfed a bit for some reason, they said that bards get all of the best stuff, </span></blockquote>
<br />
Now THAT is not true AT ALL. Bards have chronically THE WORST itemization out of all classes in the game. We have very very few instruments (read: focus effects) to choose from and those are hard to come by. Designers tend to forget about us and what we end up with is weapons with +BS% and an instrument effect that gets auto'd to rogues... <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />. Or itemization sucks. Period.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">best aa's, </span></blockquote>
<br />
Wrong again. We get a small numbers of AAs that make up for how much the majority of them suck. Fading Memories and Boastful Bellow are the one's you'll hear most about. Our instrument masteries and cap-raisers, while nice, are like a slap in the face. The instrument masteries because while they increase the power of the average bard, do nothing to high end bards with high end instruments, squishing everyone to the top of the power-ceiling bards are stuck beneath. The cap-raisers because there should be no cap--bards have no way of scaling in power the way every single other class does. We have a good number of AAs that are absolutely worthless and have actually been proclaimed &quot;This is NOT working as intended&quot; by devs, but the issue has yet to be addressed.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">and they have one of the best epics.</span></blockquote>
<br />
And wrong again. We don't have one of the best epics, just  the most necessary. Pre-Time, the epic is the only way to increase all of our instrument modifiers to 1.8, which is a major difference--+80% effectiveness to all our songs. Other classes have the option to bag their epics very soon as the progress into Planes of Power, but we don't. Not because the epic is any good--the ratio downright sucks--but because we simply have no options. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Just wondering, what would you say if they actually nerfed bards??</span></blockquote>
<br />
I wouldn't be surprised at all. Considering how little they (SOE) understand about bards, they would probably break something and just call it &quot;balancing&quot; because they're too lazy/confused to fix it. Aside from a few particular problems--itemization, broken AAs, dps balance--I am perfectly happy with my bard and would prefer that they don't touch them lest they finally break them beyond all recognition.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
