				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't think anyone's going to nerf bards soon. When you consider how much bards can do compared with most classes it is a lot more, granted. What you don't take into consideration just comparing is the difficulty of actually being able to do all of these things effectively. Take into consideration the fact that a bad bard can also get a group killed faster than you can say &quot;is he even twisting?&quot; Trust me I've seen it. Alot. This may be tooting my own horn so to speak but hey I'm only human, it takes some serious determination to really utilize a bard, and I thnk just based on that we are not overpowered. You can't take just anyone and plop them down in front of a comp with a lvl 65 bard and 200 AAs and watch them solo dragons, the only thing you're going to watch is someone dying, fast. They're just not as accessible as most classes, this has a balancing effect in itself. 
<br />

<br />
My humble opinion, lord knows I'm wrong now and then. 
